algorithm_technique: Graph cycle detection (DFS) on color dependencies
problem_summary_simple: Determine if a grid can be printed by coloring rectangles with unique colors.
problem_summary_technical: Models color dependencies as a graph; checks for cycles to ensure valid printing order.
key_insights: Each color must form a solid rectangle.
A color cannot be used if it's covered by another color that must be printed later.
This dependency can be modeled as a directed graph where an edge from color A to color B means A must be printed before B.
